text ‹Extract a φ-type assertion with potential remainders from a ‹*›-sequence of φ-types.
  Extracting a φ-type assertion (with potential remainders) from a φ-type assertion, is not
  its job, but the usual transformation reasoning (the one having no tags) of the source φ-type.
›

text ‹The canonical form is where all permission annotation are on leaves.
  It minimizes fragments. (TODO: move this)›

text ‹Log:
The assumption of identity element is strong. Consider a transformation functor whose container algebra
is unital but element algebra is not. The container goes to 𝒜SE and leads us to apply 𝒜SE on the
elements also, but that is wrong. We cannot assume the element algebra is also unital.
So then, instead of splitting the case of unitral elements or not, why not from the very beginning
we only assume non-unital algebra and use 𝒜SEi only?
›

text ‹𝒜SEi is for algebras having no identity element.
  The reasoning cannot assume the it always remains something and set that
  to the identity element if it actually doesn't remain anything.
  It causes the reasoning essentially changed because we need to use a conditional boolean flag
  ‹◒[Cw] W› to case-analysis if the remainder is produced or not.

  ‹𝒜SEa› is for the algebras that are not even associative. The separation extraction is totally
  degenerated to one-to-one transformation of each separated cells.

  We use the two actions because they are essentially three different reasoning procedures.
  Their forms of goal are different.

― ‹𝒜SE : \<^prop>‹x ⦂ Source ∗ Further_Work 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 f(x) ⦂ Target ∗ Remain 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 some @tag 𝒜SE››
▪ 𝒜SEi: ‹x ⦂ ● Source ∗ ◒[Cw] Further 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 f(x) ⦂ ● Target ∗ ◒[Cr] Remain 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 some @tag 𝒜SEi›
    ‹●› inserts it into a unital algebra.
(*𝒜SEa: \<^prop>‹x ⦂ Source ∗ Further 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 f(x) ⦂ Target 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 some @tag 𝒜SEa›
    It doesn't has the remain part because it cannot has because it is non-associative.
    It must has some unsolved further work because it is separation extraction, of form
      \<^prop>‹A * B 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 y ⦂ U›, not the simple transformation of form \<^prop>‹x ⦂ T 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 y ⦂ U›.
      To consume ‹A›, the transformation of ‹B› to ‹y ⦂ U› must remain some further work.*)

    Note non-associativity also implies non-commutativity, as in our formalization there is no
    algebra that is non-associative but commutative.
›

text ‹TODO: move›

text ‹Task of Structural Extract \<^prop>‹(x,w) ⦂ T ∗ W 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 (y,r) ⦂ U ∗ R 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 P2 @tag 𝒜SE ›,
  given \<^term>‹x ⦂ T›, expecting \<^term>‹y ⦂ U›, the reasoner finds the further element \<^term>‹w ⦂ W›
  that needs to be extracted further and the remain \<^term>‹r ⦂ R› that remains from the extraction.
  \<^prop>‹x ⦂ (Source ∗ Further_Task) 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 f(x) ⦂ (Target ∗ Remain) 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 some_info›.

  The original assertion was in a good form, but after the structural extraction, the form is destroyed.
  Many procedure application or ToA application just change the value (the abstract object) while
  the type structure is basically unchanged. If we can, after the application, recover the original
  form by some reverse transformation, it would be great.

  \<^term>‹Auto_Transform_Hint› is for this.
  \<^prop>‹ x ⦂ (Source ∗ Further_Task) 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 f(x) ⦂ (Target ∗ Remain) 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 (
        Auto_Transform_Hint (y' ⦂ From_the_Target ∗ With_the_Remains)
                            (x' ⦂ Recover_the_Source ∗ With_works_to_be_recovered_further) ∧ True
    ) @tag 𝒜SE ›
  The ‹the_Target› is a pattern having same constant and the rough structure with the ‹Target›.
  Many SE rules are equipped with a version with Auto_Transform_Hint. The rules maintains the patterns
  ‹the_Target› and ‹the_Source›, and later the system can pattern-match ‹the_Target› after
  the application to instantiate the original form ‹the_Source› and then recover it by a To-Transformation.

  The ‹Auto_Transform_Hint› only gives syntactic hint. The ‹y'› and ‹x'› are never used and can be any thing.
›

subsubsection ‹Bi-Conditioned Product›

text ‹ Motivation: 
The process presented in this section does not enlarge decision-ability of the reasoning system.
However, it can keep the expressions of abstract objects clean and neat, improving the chance of
successes of automatic proving over the objects, and reducing the proving time.

Many operations such as memory load and store does not change the structure of the abstract objects
nor the ‹φ›-types, but at most changing the values of certain elements of the objects in place.
Standard reasoning process, however, have to destruct the structure and later reconstruct the structure
maybe by user hints, causing the expression of the abstract objects got messed and lost of control.

The section presents structure-preserving transformation mappers allowing specifying abstract mapping
function by which we can apply the mapping over the abstract objects to carry out the operation without
modifying the structure nor the ‹φ›-type at all. It also supports change-free reading operation which
extracts the values of certain elements, as the reading is a mapping of identity morphism.

A limitation over the mapping is, it must be independent between the elements of the object, i.e,
if separations of the elements are represented by ‹(∗)› and related to tuples, a mapping ‹f› over
the tuples must can be represented as ‹f = map_prod f⇩1 f⇩2›  where ‹f⇩1, f⇩2› are independent mappings
for each elements. The limitation is because, the object ‹x ⦂ T› can be separated ‹x ⦂ T ≡ (x⇩1, x⇩2) ⦂ T⇩1 ∗ T⇩2›
with its elements ‹x⇩i ⦂ T⇩i› scattered over everywhere. The reasoning of transformation mappers can gather
the elements together but the mappings over the elements still have to be independent because later
we need to translate the mapping onto the scattered elements in the original form, where each scattered
element does not know where are the other elements so hard to fetch the value of the other elements if
we still want the expressions of the elements neat (otherwise, one can directly use the existing
destructing-and-reconstructing method).

›

            𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗌𝗍 (residue 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗌[C⇩R] R) 𝖿𝗈𝗋 (redex 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗌[C⇩R] R) 𝖿𝗋𝗈𝗆 Src 𝗍𝗈 Ret›

abbreviation ToA_Subst'' :: ‹'c BI ⇒ 'c BI ⇒ 'c::sep_magma BI ⇒ bool ⇒ 'c BI ⇒ bool ⇒ 'c BI ⇒ 'c BI ⇒ 'c BI ⇒ 'c BI ⇒ bool›
                          ("𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗌𝗍 _ 𝖿𝗈𝗋 _ 𝖿𝗋𝗈𝗆 _ 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗂𝗇𝗀[_] _ 𝖽𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗇𝗀[_] _ 𝗍𝗈 _ 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗂𝗇𝗀 _ 𝖽𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗇𝗀 _" [19,19,19,19,19,19,19,19,19,19] 18)
  where ‹𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗌𝗍 residue 𝖿𝗈𝗋 redex 𝖿𝗋𝗈𝗆 Src 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗂𝗇𝗀[C⇩R] R 𝖽𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗇𝗀[C⇩W] W 𝗍𝗈 Ret 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗂𝗇𝗀 W' 𝖽𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗇𝗀 R' ≡
            𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗌𝗍 (residue 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗌[C⇩R] R') 𝖿𝗈𝗋 (redex 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗌[C⇩R] R) 𝖿𝗋𝗈𝗆 (Src 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗌[C⇩W] W) 𝗍𝗈 (Ret 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗌[C⇩W] W')›

definition ToA_Mapper :: ‹('a ⇒ 'b) ⇒ ('c::sep_magma, 'a) φ ⇒ ('c,'b) φ
                       ⇒ ('x ⇒ 'y) ⇒ ('c,'x) φ ⇒ ('c,'y) φ ⇒ ('x ⇒ 'a) ⇒ ('b ⇒ 'y) ⇒ 'x set ⇒ bool›
                          ("𝗆𝖺𝗉 (_ :/ _ ↦/ _)/ 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 (_ :/ _ ↦/ _)/ 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 (𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 _/ 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 _)/ 𝗂𝗇 _" [21,21,21,21,21,21,21,21,21] 18)
  where ‹𝗆𝖺𝗉 g : U ↦ U' 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : T ↦ T' 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s 𝗂𝗇 domain ≡
            (∀x ∈ domain. x ⦂ T 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 h x ⦂ U) ∧
            (∀y ∈ g ` h ` domain. y ⦂ U' 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 s y ⦂ T') ∧
            (∀x ∈ domain. f x = s (g (h x)))›

lemma ToA_Mapper_rev_def[no_atp]:
  ‹(𝗆𝖺𝗉 g : U ↦ U' 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : T ↦ T' 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s 𝗂𝗇 domain) ⟷
      (∀x ∈ domain. x ⦂ T 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 h x ⦂ U) ∧
      (∀y ∈ g ` h ` domain. y ⦂ U' 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 s y ⦂ T') ∧
      (∀x ∈ domain. s (g (h x)) = f x)›
  unfolding ToA_Mapper_def by clarsimp fastforce

abbreviation ToA_Getter :: ‹('x ⇒ 'a) ⇒ ('c::sep_magma, 'x) φ ⇒ ('c,'a) φ ⇒ 'x set ⇒ ('a ⇒ 'x) ⇒ bool›
                           ("𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 _ : _ ↦ _ 𝗂𝗇 _ 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 _" [21,21,21,21,21] 18)
  where ‹𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h : T ↦ U 𝗂𝗇 domain 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s ≡

lemma ToA_Mapper_onward:
  ‹ 𝗆𝖺𝗉 g : U ↦ U' 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : T ↦ T' 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s 𝗂𝗇 D
⟹ 𝗉𝗋𝖾𝗆𝗂𝗌𝖾 x ∈ D
⟹ x ⦂ T 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 h x ⦂ U›
  unfolding ToA_Mapper_def Premise_def
  by (clarsimp simp add: φProd_expn'')

lemma ToA_Mapper_backward:
  ‹ 𝗆𝖺𝗉 g : U ↦ U' 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : T ↦ T' 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s 𝗂𝗇 D
⟹ 𝗉𝗋𝖾𝗆𝗂𝗌𝖾 x ∈ g ` h ` D
⟹ x ⦂ U' 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 s x ⦂ T'›
  unfolding ToA_Mapper_def Premise_def
  by (clarsimp simp add: φProd_expn'')

lemma ToA_Mapper_f_expn:
  ‹ 𝗆𝖺𝗉 g : U ↦ U' 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : T ↦ T' 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s 𝗂𝗇 D
⟹ ∀x ∈ D. f x = s (g (h x)) ›
  unfolding ToA_Mapper_def
  by clarsimp

lemma ToA_Mapper_f_expn_rev[no_atp]:
  ‹ 𝗆𝖺𝗉 g : U ↦ U' 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : T ↦ T' 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s 𝗂𝗇 D
⟹ ∀x ∈ D. s (g (h x)) = f x ›
  unfolding ToA_Mapper_def
  by clarsimp

lemma ToA_Mapper_cong:
  ‹ U ≡ U'
⟹ U⇩1 ≡ U⇩1'
⟹ T ≡ T'
⟹ T⇩1 ≡ T⇩1'
⟹ D ≡ D'
⟹ (⋀x. x ∈ D' ⟹ f x ≡ f' x)
⟹ (⋀x. x ∈ D' ⟹ h x ≡ h' x)
⟹ (⋀x. x ∈ h' ` D' ⟹ g x ≡ g' x)
⟹ (⋀x. x ∈ g' ` h' ` D' ⟹ s x ≡ s' x)
⟹ 𝗆𝖺𝗉 g : U ↦ U⇩1 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : T ↦ T⇩1 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s 𝗂𝗇 D
 ≡ 𝗆𝖺𝗉 g' : U' ↦ U⇩1' 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f' : T' ↦ T⇩1' 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h' 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s' 𝗂𝗇 D'›
  unfolding ToA_Mapper_def atomize_eq
  by (clarsimp simp add: image_iff Bex_def; rule; clarsimp; metis)

lemma ToA_Mapper_φSome_rewr_origin[no_atp]:
  ‹ NO_MATCH (● UUU) U
⟹ 𝗆𝖺𝗉 g : U ↦ U' 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : T ↦ T' 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s 𝗂𝗇 domain
 ≡ 𝗆𝖺𝗉 g : ● U ↦ ● U' 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : ● T ↦ ● T' 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s 𝗂𝗇 domain ›
  unfolding ToA_Mapper_def φSome_transformation_strip .


lemma ToA_Mapper_LPR_gen_cong:
  ‹ D ≡ D'
⟹ (⋀x. x ∈ D' ⟹ h x ≡ h' x)
⟹ (⋀x. x ∈ g ` h' ` D' ⟹ s x ≡ s' x)
⟹ 𝗆𝖺𝗉 g : U ↦ U⇩1 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : T ↦ T⇩1 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s 𝗂𝗇 D
  ≡ 𝗆𝖺𝗉 g : U ↦ U⇩1 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : T ↦ T⇩1 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h' 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s' 𝗂𝗇 D'›
  unfolding ToA_Mapper_def atomize_eq
  by (clarsimp simp add: image_iff Bex_def; rule; clarsimp; metis)

subsubsection ‹Programming Method›

lemma [φreason %φprogramming_method]:
  ‹ PROP φProgramming_Method
      (∀x. 𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 x ∈ D ⟶ (x ⦂ T 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 h x ⦂ U) &&&
       ∀x. 𝖼𝗈𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗍𝗂𝗈𝗇 x ∈ g ` h ` D ⟶ (x ⦂ U' 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 s x ⦂ T') &&&
       ∀x ∈ D. f x = s (g (h x)))
      MM DD RR FF
⟹ PROP φProgramming_Method
      (Trueprop (𝗆𝖺𝗉 g : U ↦ U' 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : T ↦ T' 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s 𝗂𝗇 D)) MM DD RR FF ›
  unfolding φProgramming_Method_def Premise_def
  subgoal premises prems
    by (insert prems(1)[OF ‹PROP DD› ‹PROP RR› ‹PROP FF›];
        clarsimp simp add: conjunction_imp ToA_Mapper_def ToA_Subst_def) .

definition ‹subst_sp C U T S S' direction ― ‹True for splitting target›
                     C⇩R R R' C⇩W W W'
  ⟷  (if C
        then 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗌𝗍 U 𝖿𝗈𝗋 T 𝖿𝗋𝗈𝗆 S 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗂𝗇𝗀[C⇩R] R 𝖽𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗇𝗀[C⇩W] W 𝗍𝗈 S' 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗂𝗇𝗀 W' 𝖽𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗇𝗀 R'
        else if direction
        then (C⇩R, R, R', C⇩W, W, W') = (False, ⊤, ⊤, True, T, U)
        else (C⇩R, R, R', R, C⇩W, W, W') = (True, S, S', S', False, ⊤, ⊤))›

definition ‹getter_sp C T M C⇩R R C⇩W W direction
  ⟷ (if C
       then 𝗀𝖾𝗍 T 𝖿𝗋𝗈𝗆 M 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗂𝗇𝗀[C⇩R] R 𝖽𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗇𝗀[C⇩W] W
       else if direction
       then (W, C⇩W, C⇩R, R) = (T, True, False, ⊤)
       else (W, C⇩W, C⇩R, R) = (⊤, False, True, M)) ›

                      and ‹getter_sp ?C _ _ _ _ _ _ ?direction› ⇒

  ‹ 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗌𝗍 U 𝖿𝗈𝗋 T 𝖿𝗋𝗈𝗆 S 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗂𝗇𝗀[C⇩R] R 𝖽𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗇𝗀[C⇩W] W 𝗍𝗈 S' 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗂𝗇𝗀 W' 𝖽𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗇𝗀 R'
⟹ subst_sp True U T S S' Any
              C⇩R R R' C⇩W W W' ›

lemma [φreason %φmapToA_init]:
  ‹ 𝗆𝖺𝗉 g : U ∗[C⇩R] R ↦ U' ∗[C⇩R] R' 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : T ∗[C⇩W] W ↦ T' ∗[C⇩W] W' 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s 𝗂𝗇 {(x,w)}
⟹ 𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖿𝗒[𝗌𝖺𝖿𝖾] ret : h (x, w)
⟹ 𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖿𝗒[𝗌𝖺𝖿𝖾] ret⇩f : f (x, w)
⟹ 𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖿𝗒[𝗌𝖺𝖿𝖾] ret⇩1 : fst ret
⟹ 𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖿𝗒[𝗌𝖺𝖿𝖾] ret⇩2 : snd ret
⟹ 𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖿𝗒[𝗌𝖺𝖿𝖾] ret⇩f⇩1 : fst ret⇩f
⟹ 𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖿𝗒[𝗌𝖺𝖿𝖾] ret⇩f⇩2 : snd ret⇩f
⟹ 𝖽𝗈 lookup_a_mapper g ret (y', r')
⟹ 𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗌𝗍 y' ⦂ U' 𝖿𝗈𝗋 ret⇩1 ⦂ U 𝖿𝗋𝗈𝗆 x ⦂ T 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗂𝗇𝗀[C⇩R] ret⇩2 ⦂ R 𝖽𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗇𝗀[C⇩W] w ⦂ W
      𝗍𝗈 ret⇩f⇩1 ⦂ T' 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗂𝗇𝗀 ret⇩f⇩2 ⦂ W' 𝖽𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗇𝗀 r' ⦂ R' ›
  unfolding ToA_Mapper_def ToA_Subst_def Premise_def Simplify_def
            lookup_a_mapper_def Simplify_def
  by (cases C⇩R; cases C⇩W; clarsimp simp add: φProd_expn'' φProd_expn'; metis fst_eqD snd_conv)

lemma [φreason %φmapToA_init+10]:
  ‹ 𝗆𝖺𝗉 g ⊗⇩f r⇩f : U ∗[C⇩R] R ↦ U ∗[C⇩R] R
    𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f ⊗⇩f w⇩f : T ∗[C⇩W] W ↦ T ∗[C⇩W] W
    𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s 𝗂𝗇 {(x,w)}
⟹ mapToA_assign_id g
⟹ mapToA_assign_id f
⟹ if C⇩R then mapToA_assign_id r⇩f else True
⟹ if C⇩W then mapToA_assign_id w⇩f else True
⟹ 𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖿𝗒[𝗌𝖺𝖿𝖾] ret : h (x, w)
⟹ 𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖿𝗒[𝗌𝖺𝖿𝖾] ret⇩1 : fst ret
⟹ 𝗌𝗂𝗆𝗉𝗅𝗂𝖿𝗒[𝗌𝖺𝖿𝖾] ret⇩2 : snd ret
⟹ 𝗉𝗋𝖾𝗆𝗂𝗌𝖾 ret⇩1 = y
⟹ 𝗀𝖾𝗍 y ⦂ U 𝖿𝗋𝗈𝗆 x ⦂ T 𝗋𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗂𝗇𝗂𝗇𝗀[C⇩R] ret⇩2 ⦂ R 𝖽𝖾𝗆𝖺𝗇𝖽𝗂𝗇𝗀[C⇩W] w ⦂ W ›
  unfolding ToA_Extract_def ToA_Mapper_def BI_eq_ToA Premise_def mapToA_assign_id_def
            Simplify_rev_def
  by (cases C⇩R; cases C⇩W; clarsimp simp add: φProd_expn'' φProd_expn'; metis fst_eqD snd_conv)

definition ‹ToAmap_assign_empty C⇩R r h s R R' r⇩x h⇩x s⇩x R⇩x R'⇩x ⟷
  (∀g f D U U' T T'.
     (𝗆𝖺𝗉 g ⊗⇩f r : U ∗[C⇩R] R ↦ U' ∗[C⇩R] R'
      𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : T ↦ T'
      𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s 𝗂𝗇 D) ⟶
     (𝗆𝖺𝗉 g ⊗⇩f r⇩x : U ∗ R⇩x ↦ U' ∗ R'⇩x
      𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : T ↦ T'
      𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h⇩x 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s⇩x 𝗂𝗇 D))›

definition ‹ToAmap_assign_empty_src C⇩W h s W W' D w h⇩x s⇩x D⇩x ⟷
  (∀g f U U' T T'.
      (𝗆𝖺𝗉 g : U ↦ U' 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f ⊗⇩f w : T ∗[C⇩W] W ↦ T' ∗[C⇩W] W'
       𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s 𝗂𝗇 D⇩x) ⟶
      (𝗆𝖺𝗉 g : U ↦ U' 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 f : T ↦ T'
       𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 h⇩x 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 s⇩x 𝗂𝗇 D))›

lemma [φreason %ToAmap_assign_empty_src]:
  ‹ Identity_Elements⇩E W  D⇩E
⟹ Identity_Elements⇩I W' D⇩I P⇩I
⟹ 𝗉𝗋𝖾𝗆𝗂𝗌𝖾 (∀x. D⇩E x ⟷ x = ε) ∧ (D⇩I (w ε))
⟹ ToAmap_assign_empty_src True h s W W' D w (λx. h (x, ε)) (fst o s) (D × {ε}) ›
  for W :: ‹('c::sep_magma_1, 'w) φ›
  unfolding ToAmap_assign_empty_src_def Identity_Elements⇩E_def Identity_Elements⇩I_def
            Identity_Element⇩E_def Identity_Element⇩I_def Premise_def
  by (auto simp: ToA_Mapper_def Transformation_def prod.map_beta,
      metis mult_1_class.mult_1_right sep_magma_1_left,
      metis mult_1_class.mult_1_right snd_conv,
      metis fst_conv)

fun transformation_counter' bvtys concl =
  case try Phi_Syntax.dest_transformation concl
    of SOME (S,T,_) => SOME (Phi_Syntax.number_of_typ_operators_in_assertion bvtys S +
                             Phi_Syntax.number_of_typ_operators_in_assertion bvtys T )
     | _ => (
  case try Phi_Syntax.dest_ToA_Extract concl
    of SOME (S, T) => SOME (Phi_Syntax.number_of_typ_operators_in_assertion bvtys S +
                            Phi_Syntax.number_of_typ_operators_in_assertion bvtys T )
     | _ => (
  case try Phi_Syntax.dest_ToA_Subst concl
    of SOME (A,B,C,D) => SOME ( Phi_Syntax.number_of_typ_operators_in_assertion bvtys A +
                                Phi_Syntax.number_of_typ_operators_in_assertion bvtys B +
                                Phi_Syntax.number_of_typ_operators_in_assertion bvtys C +
                                Phi_Syntax.number_of_typ_operators_in_assertion bvtys D )
     | _ => (
  case try Phi_Syntax.dest_ToA_Mapper concl
    of SOME (_,U,U',_,T,T',_,_,_) =>
          SOME (Phi_Syntax.number_of_typ_operators bvtys U +
                Phi_Syntax.number_of_typ_operators bvtys T )
     | _ => NONE
  )))

fun transformation_counter thm =
  let val (bvtys, concl) = Phi_Help.strip_meta_hhf_bvtys (Phi_Help.leading_antecedent' thm)
   in transformation_counter' bvtys concl
   |> Option.map (fn n => (if n = 0 then () else (); n))
  end

val _ = (
  PLPR_Statistics.add_subgoal_counter (\<^pattern_prop>‹_ 𝗍𝗋𝖺𝗇𝗌𝖿𝗈𝗋𝗆𝗌 _ 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 _›, transformation_counter) ;
  PLPR_Statistics.add_subgoal_counter (\<^pattern_prop>‹𝗀𝖾𝗍 _ 𝖿𝗋𝗈𝗆 _›, transformation_counter) ;
  PLPR_Statistics.add_subgoal_counter (\<^pattern_prop>‹𝗌𝗎𝖻𝗌𝗍 _ 𝖿𝗈𝗋 _ 𝖿𝗋𝗈𝗆 _ 𝗍𝗈 _›, transformation_counter) ;
  PLPR_Statistics.add_subgoal_counter (\<^pattern_prop>‹𝗆𝖺𝗉 _ : _ ↦ _ 𝗈𝗏𝖾𝗋 _ : _ ↦ _ 𝗐𝗂𝗍𝗁 𝗀𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 _ 𝗌𝖾𝗍𝗍𝖾𝗋 _ 𝗂𝗇 _›, transformation_counter)
)
